If you intend serving Rhine and Moselle this com- ing summer, don’t overlook this list. It must be remembered that the German mark has been re- valued upwards by 8%; the better wines of 1966 and 1967 are becoming scarce, thus forcing the prices upwards, and shipping costs have gone up. All this will surely be reflected in higher prices next summer. Obviously now is the time to acquire these wines.
